The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Thursday, July 15, 2004  The City Diary
																																																																																		The Barasat Police on Wednesday arrested a 16-year-old boy for attempting to molest a student of Class IV. The arrested, Rabin Biswas, is a resident of Nabapally, Banbania in Ashoknagar. According to the police, Biswas had been stalking the girl for days. 																																																								he victims father is missing and she is taken care of by her mother. On Wednesday afternoon, the mother had gone out for work leaving the girl alone at home. Biswas took advantage of the mothers absence, slipped into the house and allegedly tried to molest the girl. The matter came to light after the girls mother returned and the police were subsequently informed. 																																																		In a rare display of honesty, a taxi driver returned to the police an expensive camera which he found on the backseat of his car. The incident took place at the intersection of AJC Bose Road and Shakespeare Sarani around 1.15 pm on Wednesday. Minutes before the discovery, the driver  Ram Sadhan Mukhia, a resident of Lake Camp, near Rabindra Sarobar  had dropped an unidentified person who had hired the taxi. Soon after the man left, Mukhia discovered the camera which the passenger had left behind and decided to hand it over to the cops. 																																																		 A 32-year-old woman, Seema Haldar was killed and nine others were seriously injured when they were hit by a private bus on Diamond Harbour Road on Wednesday. Police said Haldar died on the spot and the injured were admitted to hospital. The killer vehicle was impounded but the driver had fled.																																																		Traffic was disrupted for more than an hour on Wednesday morning when the residents of Barrackpore Feeder Road put up a blockade to protest the deteriorating condition of the stretch. The blockade affected both pedestrians and vehicles. Residents alleged that accidents have become a regular feature in the area owing to the deplorable condition of Barrackpore Road and the Kalyani Expressway.																																																		 Indian Medical Association (IMA) on Wednesday condemned the manner in which Bharati Mitra, a doctor at a Calcutta Municipal Corporation-run maternity home in Kidderpore, was sacked on Tuesday on charges of dereliction of duty. Moloy Patra, state secretary of the IMA, said she was dismissed from service quite unceremoniously. 							LARSEN AND TOUBRO for organising a run for a clean and green Calcutta on July 4 from Victoria Memorial to Shakespeare Sarani
